<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 4:51PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorm wind gusts will impact portions of
northeastern Blaine County through 530 PM MDT...
At 449 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorm wind
gusts along the Canadian border. Movement was southeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Turner and Hogeland.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
